t. The redirect endpoint parses the target URL, validates any netloc against the current host, and either rejects external URLs with a 400 error or performs the redirect with a 302 status code. parsed = urlparse(target_url)\n    \n    # If it has a netloc (domain/host), validate it matches current host\n    if parsed.netloc:\n        # Extract hostname without port for comparison\n        target_host = parsed.netloc.split(':')[0]\n        current_host = request.host.split(':')[0]\n        \n        if target_host != current_host:\n            return \"target_url must be internal\", 400\n    \n    # Redirect to the target URL with 302 status\n    return redirect(target_url, code=302)\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    app.run()\n```\n\nThe implementation parses the URL to check if it contains a domain, and if so, compares the hostname against the current request's host to ensure it's internal. If the hosts don't match, it returns a 400 error. For valid internal URLs, it performs a 302 redirect using Flask's redirect function.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4666,"cache_read_input_tokens":24095,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4666},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c90dfc0-3684-44d0-a193-f5d2abe73d9c","uuid":"1884f1a8-559c-4e03-8032-3265db253ebc","request_id":"req_011CbdLwRxGwVgSaSk4k71sm"}
